  <title>Explosive crater twins on Mars</title>
  <description><![CDATA[
                <img src="http://esa.int/var/esa/storage/images/esa_multimedia/images/2013/04/arima_twins/12612928-3-eng-GB/Arima_twins_small.jpg" width="170" height="96" align="left" hspace="8" /><br />
    <p>
Dramatic underground explosions, perhaps involving ice, are responsible for the pits inside these two large martian impact craters, imaged by ESA’s Mars Express on 4 January.
</p>
  ]]></description>
